# reading csv
df = pd.read_csv('Conditions_Contributing_to_COVID-19_Deaths__by_State_and_Age__Provisional_2020-2023.csv')

# removing unecessary data
df = df[df['Group'] == 'By Month']
df = df[(df['Age Group'] != 'All Ages') & (df['Age Group'] != 'Not stated')]

# merging "year" and "month" into one column
df['Year'] += (df['Month'] - 1) / 12

# deleting unecessary columns
del df['Group']
del df['Start Date']
del df['End Date']
del df['Data As Of']
del df['Flag']
del df['ICD10_codes']
del df['Number of Mentions']
del df['Month']

# removing unusable data
df.dropna(axis='index', inplace=True)
df = df[df['State'] != 'United States']  # different measurement techniques by CDC make this data 
                                         # uncomparable to state-specific data

def normDeathsByCol(frame, col):
    # Adds a column to "frame" which represents the percent/100 of all covid deaths in
    # col(s) which are due to each row.
    
    new = pd.DataFrame()
    
    for tag, group in frame.groupby(col):
        total = group['COVID-19 Deaths'].sum()
        group['norm'] = group['COVID-19 Deaths'] / total if total != 0.0 else 0.0
        new = pd.concat([new, group])
    
    return new

def diffFromAvg(frame, total):
    # Adds a column to "frame" which represents the difference between the normalized deaths
    # of each row and the normalized deaths of the United States for that year,condition, and
    # age group.
    
    total = total.copy()
    total['diff'] = total['norm']
    frame = frame.merge(total, how='right', on=['Year', 'Condition Group', 'Condition', 'Age Group'])
    del frame['COVID-19 Deaths_y']
    del frame['norm_y']
    frame = frame.rename(columns={'COVID-19 Deaths_x':'COVID-19 Deaths', 'norm_x':'norm'})
    frame['diff'] = frame['norm'] - frame['diff']
    return frame

df = normDeathsByCol(df, ['Year', 'State', 'Age Group'])
natltotal = normDeathsByCol(natltotal, ['Year', 'Age Group'])
df = diffFromAvg(df, natltotal)

In [6]:
rolling_avg_size = 5

for age, d1 in natltotal.groupby('Age Group'):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
    plt.title(age)
    
    for cnd, d2 in d1.groupby('Condition Group'):
        if cnd in ['COVID-19']:
            continue
        
        plt.plot(d2['Year'], d2['norm'].rolling(rolling_avg_size).mean(), label=f'{cnd}')
    
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(linestyle='--')
    plt.show()

for cnd, d1 in df.groupby('Condition Group'):
    if cnd in ['All other conditions and causes (residual)', 'COVID-19']:
        continue
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
    plt.title(cnd)
    #plt.grid(linestyle='--')
    data = pd.DataFrame(columns=['State', 'diff'])
    
    for state, d2 in d1.groupby('State'):
        if state == 'United States':
            continue
        new = pd.DataFrame({'State': [state], 'diff': [d2['diff'].mean()]})
        data = pd.concat([data, new], ignore_index=True)

    bar = sns.barplot(data=data, x='State', y='diff')
    bar.set_xticklabels(bar.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right")
    plt.gca().yaxis.grid(False)
    plt.gca().xaxis.grid(True)
    
    plt.show()
